the native launch surfaces are.

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:05.770
So on mobile, usually
from the home screen.

00:02:05.770 --> 00:02:10.433
Install aligns to a user's
mental model for how install--

00:02:10.433 --> 00:02:12.850
basically, how experiences
ought to operate on the device.

00:02:12.850 --> 00:02:16.900
An installed web app looks and
feels like every other app.

00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:19.450
And the fact that your user
discovered and installed

00:02:19.450 --> 00:02:22.120
your app from the
browser or from Play

00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:24.070
shouldn't actually
matter when they go back

00:02:24.070 --> 00:02:26.090
to use your app again.

00:02:26.090 --> 00:02:29.200
Most importantly, the word
install signals to users

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:32.005
that the experience was meant
to be great on their device.

00:02:38.607 --> 00:02:40.190
Here's a summary of
how web install is

00:02:40.190 --> 00:02:41.650
different from bookmarks.

00:02:41.650 --> 00:02:44.410
Web install offers
users access to web apps

00:02:44.410 --> 00:02:45.880
from familiar
discovery and launch

00:02:45.880 --> 00:02:47.710
surfaces for their device.

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:49.448
So install web apps
can be standalone.

00:02:49.448 --> 00:02:51.490
That means they can be
separate from the browser.

00:02:51.490 --> 00:02:54.190
It also means that they can be
integrated into the native task

00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:55.060
switcher.

00:02:55.060 --> 00:02:58.030
And they can-- this is gonna be
a more familiar way for users

00:02:58.030 --> 00:02:59.470
to interact with
apps, or it might

00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:03.180
be more suitable to certain
types of tasks than tabs.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.140
Web install integrates
the web apps

00:03:05.140 --> 00:03:08.270
with the device services
that expect an installed app.

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:11.140
The important thing to remember
when you're asking a user

00:03:11.140 --> 00:03:13.690
to install a PWA is that
with an installed app,

00:03:13.690 --> 00:03:16.030
you're telling the user that
it is an experience that

00:03:16.030 --> 00:03:18.190
is meant for the device
that the user is using,

00:03:18.190 --> 00:03:19.360
and that means that
you need to live up

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:21.068
to those expectations
of what you design,

00:03:21.068 --> 00:03:22.850
or you're going to
have unhappy users.

00:03:22.850 --> 00:03:25.183
There's a good thing that we
have a pattern for building

00:03:25.183 --> 00:03:27.540
experiences that do just that.

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:30.600
Progressive Web Apps are
a pattern for great apps

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:31.860
that use web technology.

00:03:31.860 --> 00:03:33.860
And they have all the
features and functionality

00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:36.240
users expect from a modern
app on mobile or desktop.

00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:37.740
I'm sure most of
you in this room

00:03:37.740 --> 00:03:39.550
are quite familiar with
PWAs at this point,

00:03:39.550 --> 00:03:42.270
so I'll just cover some of
the very high level background

00:03:42.270 --> 00:03:44.370
information about PWAs
for those of you who

00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:46.323
maybe are new to the concept.

00:03:46.323 --> 00:03:48.240
PWAs include things like
personalized content,

00:03:48.240 --> 00:03:50.250
offline mode, push
notifications,

00:03:50.250 --> 00:03:51.510
and instant loading.

00:03:51.510 --> 00:03:54.460
And PWAs and installed web
apps do go hand in hand.

00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:57.910
You need to have a PWA in
order to offer install.

00:03:57.910 --> 00:03:59.487
There are, of course,
other projects

00:03:59.487 --> 00:04:01.070
that are trying to
crack this problem,

00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:04.513
and you can take a look at React
Native, at Electron or Cordova.

00:04:04.513 --> 00:04:06.305
And all of these are
basically offering you

00:04:06.305 --> 00:04:09.300
a way to build native
apps using web technology,

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:12.060
but those experiences do depend
on functionality that won't

00:04:12.060 --> 00:04:13.850
also work in the web browser.

00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:16.617
PWA's goal is to build
directly on the web.

00:04:16.617 --> 00:04:18.450
So that means you can
maintain one code base

00:04:18.450 --> 00:04:21.720
and that's going to work for
visitors both in the browser

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:23.430
as well as for your
installed users.

